{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B end-to-end boot probe (runs as the kernel init, additive). As a descendant of the gate-aware kernel-root it inherits the portal: it mmaps the inherited region memfd (fd 5, MAP_SHARED) to get the region base, sets g_portal_region_base, renders the tool_request OBJECT from its config to a single string at the boundary, submits it through the portal (transmit-request-through-portal-region-awaiting-reply, using the inherited request/response eventfds fd3/fd4), and writes the reply read back from the region to an output file. The output path and the tool request OBJECT come from its own request (config data). Proves the kernel serves real tools through the portal under a real boot and that a cross-execve descendant can submit by mmapping fd5.","module_name":"probe-portal-serve-reply-storing-output-document","package_name":"probe-portal-serve-reply-storing-output-document","function_definitions":{"probe-portal-serve-reply-storing-output-document":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"prot","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"mapshared","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c16384","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16384},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_out","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation